<p>Franklin D. Roosevelt, the 32nd president of the United States, was born on 1/30/1882, in Hyde Park, New York. He was 51 when he took office on 3/4/1933. Member: Democratic Party.

	
		He died in office on 4/12/1945.
	

	His occupation before the presidency: Lawyer.
	His college: Harvard.

	
		He died in Warm Springs, Georgia, on 4/12/1945.
	
